{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871636245,"sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","part":{"id":"prt_d7a32b2d8001S2K3Gt894Gc2xO","messageID":"msg_d7a32a972001BwSe9PbT6tdlt2","sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e00b97b22890492a8d6d637335a1e98f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Command-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Global CLI options\n10: The system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n11: \n12: #### Scenario: Version display\n13: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n14: - **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n15: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n18: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n19: - **WHEN** the callback runs\n20: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n21: \n22: ### Requirement: `pack` command\n23: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n26: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n27: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n28: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Successful pack\n31: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n32: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n36: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n37: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n38: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: `build` command\n41: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n44: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n45: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n46: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n49: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n50: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n51: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Version increment on build\n54: - **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n55: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n56: - **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: `publish` command\n59: The system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n62: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n63: - **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n66: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n67: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n68: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n71: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n72: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n73: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: `invoke` command\n76: The system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n79: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n80: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Invalid payload\n83: - **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n84: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n85: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Invalid header format\n88: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n89: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n90: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n93: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n94: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n95: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: `status` command\n98: The system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n101: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n102: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Not published\n105: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n106: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n107: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\n110: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Missing workspace\n113: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n115: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n118: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n119: - **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n120: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: Metadata file format\n123: The system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Save location\n126: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n127: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n128: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Schema validation\n131: - **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n132: - **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n133: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Docker integration\n136: The system SHALL use the Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) to build images, push to a registry when configured, and optionally remove images.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Build image\n139: - **GIVEN** Docker is running\n140: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL tag `{image_name}:{tag}`, pass optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, and return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Push image\n144: - **GIVEN** a local image name and optional `registry_url` / credentials\n145: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image` runs\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL login if username and password are provided, retag when needed, stream push logs, and return `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Remove image\n149: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n150: - **WHEN** removal succeeds\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`; on failure it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — standard provider\n154: The system SHALL create or patch `Deployment` and `NodePort` `Service`, wait for rollout, report pod status, and support deletion.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Deploy agent\n157: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n158: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n159: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Wait for ready\n162: - **GIVEN** a deployment name\n163: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Delete agent\n167: - **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called\n168: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n172: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom object in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, plural `agentruntimes`.\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Deploy CR\n175: - **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n176: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment when missing in `env_vars`, set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`, and reference `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n178: \n179: ### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\n180: The system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for `provider=agentcube` publish/status flows and `KubernetesProvider` for `provider=k8s`.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Status for AgentRuntime\n183: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n184: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n185: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (`status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n188: The system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions: print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red; if `verbose`, print traceback; raise `typer.Exit(1)`.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n191: - **GIVEN** a subcommand’s local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n192: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n193: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand’s `verbose` flag\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: **Note:** The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nCommand-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Global CLI options\nThe system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n\n#### Scenario: Version display\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n\n#### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n- **WHEN** the callback runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/cli-toolkit/spec.md","time":{"start":1775871636223,"end":1775871636242}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775871636275,"sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","part":{"id":"prt_d7a32b315001O7cBctSbEy18YF","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a32a972001BwSe9PbT6tdlt2","sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":29066,"input":1353,"output":66,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":27647}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775871640954,"sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","part":{"id":"prt_d7a32c576001nxKd2FvX5eQw0d","messageID":"msg_d7a32b34d0013squ1VQytl9dcS","sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871642649,"sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","part":{"id":"prt_d7a32c97b0019Npyk3v21ZfApI","messageID":"msg_d7a32b34d0013squ1VQytl9dcS","sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3984654d7837479c821b4ae32685f685","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Successfully implemented the DockerService encapsulation for the AgentCube CLI toolkit as specified in AR-024. The implementation provides a Pythonic abstraction layer over Docker SDK operations required by the CLI's `pack`, `build`, and `publish` workflows.\n6: \n7: ## Implementation Details\n8: \n9: ### Files Modified/Created\n10: \n11: 1. **cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py** - Main implementation\n12:    - Complete DockerService class with all required methods\n13:    - Comprehensive docstrings following Google style\n14:    - Input validation and security measures\n15:    - Error handling and logging\n16: \n17: 2. **cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py** - Comprehensive test suite\n18:    - 47 test cases covering all functionality\n19:    - 98% code coverage\n20:    - Tests for success scenarios, error scenarios, and edge cases\n21: \n22: ### DockerService Class Features\n23: \n24: #### Public Methods\n25: \n26: 1. **`__init__(verbose: bool = False)`**\n27:    - Initializes Docker service with optional verbose logging\n28:    - Lazy initialization of Docker client\n29: \n30: 2. **`check_docker_available() -> bool`**\n31:    - Checks if Docker daemon is running and accessible\n32:    - Returns `True` if available, `False` otherwise\n33:    - Does not raise exceptions for availability checks\n34: \n35: 3. **`build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args) -> Dict[str, Any]`**\n36:    - Builds Docker images from Dockerfiles\n37:    - Supports build arguments for proxy configuration\n38:    - Validates input paths before building\n39:    - Returns comprehensive build metadata\n40: \n41: 4. **`get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]`**\n42:    - Retrieves image metadata (ID, size, creation time)\n43:    - Formats sizes in human-readable format\n44:    - Returns empty dict if image not found\n45: \n46: 5. **`push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password) -> Dict[str, Any]`**\n47:    - Pushes images to container registries\n48:    - Supports Docker Hub and private registries\n49:    - Handles authentication securely\n50:    - Streams push logs in verbose mode\n51: \n52: 6. **`remove_image(image_name: str, force: bool = True) -> bool`**\n53:    - Removes images from local daemon\n54:    - Returns `True` on success, `False` on failure\n55:    - Does not raise exceptions for cleanup operations\n56: \n57: #### Private Methods\n58: \n59: 1. **`_validate_build_paths(dockerfile_path, context_path)`**\n60:    - Validates file paths before Docker operations\n61:    - Prevents directory traversal attacks\n62:    - Ensures paths exist and have correct types\n63: \n64: 2. **`_format_size(size_bytes: int) -> str`**\n65:    - Formats byte sizes into human-readable format\n66:    - Supports B, KB, MB, GB, TB units\n67:    - Uses 2 decimal places for precision\n68: \n69: 3. **`_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)`**\n70:    - Authenticates with Docker registries\n71:    - Passwords are never logged or stored\n72:    - Secure credential handling\n73: \n74: 4. **`_tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image)`**\n75:    - Tags images for registry pushes\n76:    - Force tagging to overwrite existing tags\n77: \n78: ### Key Features\n79: \n80: #### Security\n81: - Passwords never logged or stored in instance variables\n82: - Path validation prevents directory traversal\n83: - Input validation for all parameters\n84: - Secure authentication through Docker SDK\n85: \n86: #### Error Handling\n87: - Comprehensive exception handling with descriptive messages\n88: - Differentiates between recoverable and non-recoverable errors\n89: - Logs warnings for non-critical issues\n90: - Raises `RuntimeError` for unrecoverable failures\n91: \n92: #### Logging\n93: - Respects `verbose` flag for detailed logging\n94: - INFO level for normal operations\n95: - DEBUG level for verbose mode\n96: - Security-conscious logging (no passwords)\n97: \n98: #### Performance\n99: - Lazy initialization of Docker client\n100: - Efficient streaming of build/push logs\n101: - No unnecessary resource consumption\n102: - Thread-safe for read operations\n103: \n104: ### Test Coverage\n105: \n106: #### Test Categories\n107: \n108: 1. **Initialization Tests** (2 tests)\n109:    - Verbose mode configuration\n110:    - Lazy client initialization\n111: \n112: 2. **Docker Availability Tests** (2 tests)\n113:    - Success scenario\n114:    - Failure scenario\n115: \n116: 3. **Build Image Tests** (11 tests)\n117:    - Success scenarios (default tag, custom tag, build_args)\n118:    - Error scenarios (Docker unavailable, build failure)\n119:    - Input validation (invalid paths, invalid image_name)\n120: \n121: 4. **Get Image Info Tests** (3 tests)\n122:    - Success scenario\n123:    - Image not found scenario\n124:    - ID truncation verification\n125: \n126: 5. **Format Size Tests** (7 tests)\n127:    - All units (B, KB, MB, GB, TB)\n128:    - Edge cases (zero, boundaries)\n129:    - Small values\n130: \n131: 6. **Push Image Tests** (6 tests)\n132:    - Default registry\n133:    - Custom registry\n134:    - With authentication\n135:    - Error scenarios\n136: \n137: 7. **Docker Login Tests** (3 tests)\n138:    - Success scenarios\n139:    - Default registry\n140:    - Authentication failure\n141: \n142: 8. **Tag Image Tests** (2 tests)\n143:    - Success scenario\n144:    - Failure scenario\n145: \n146: 9. **Remove Image Tests** (3 tests)\n147:    - Success scenario\n148:    - Failure scenario\n149:    - Force option\n150: \n151: 10. **Path Validation Tests** (5 tests)\n152:     - Valid paths\n153:     - Non-existent paths\n154:     - Invalid path types\n155: \n156: 11. **Integration Tests** (2 tests - skipped)\n157:     - End-to-end build\n158:     - End-to-end push\n159: \n160: #### Test Results\n161: \n162: - **Total Tests**: 47\n163: - **Passed**: 45\n164: - **Skipped**: 2 (integration tests requiring Docker daemon)\n165: - **Failed**: 0\n166: - **Coverage**: 98% for docker_service.py\n167: \n168: ### Integration with Existing Code\n169: \n170: #### BuildRuntime Integration\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n174: \n175: class BuildRuntime:\n176:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n177:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n178: \n179:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n180:         # Uses DockerService for local builds\n181:         result = self.docker_service.build_image(\n182:             dockerfile_path=workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\",\n183:             context_path=workspace_path,\n184:             image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n185:             tag=metadata.version or \"latest\",\n186:             build_args=options.get(\"build_args\")\n187:         )\n188: ```\n189: \n190: #### PublishRuntime Integration\n191: \n192: ```python\n193: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n194: \n195: class PublishRuntime:\n196:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n197:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n198: \n199:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n200:         # Uses DockerService for pushing images\n201:         push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n202:             image_name=image_name,\n203:             registry_url=options.get(\"registry_url\"),\n204:             username=options.get(\"image_username\"),\n205:             password=options.get(\"image_password\")\n206:         )\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### API Contract Compliance\n210: \n211: All public methods match the design specification:\n212: \n213: | Method | Input Parameters | Return Type | Exceptions |\n214: |--------|----------------|-------------|------------|\n215: | `__init__` | `verbose: bool = False` | `DockerService` | `RuntimeError` |\n216: | `check_docker_available` | - | `bool` | - |\n217: | `build_image` | `dockerfile_path`, `context_path`, `image_name`, `tag`, `build_args` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `RuntimeError`, `FileNotFoundError`, `ValueError` |\n218: | `get_image_info` | `image_name` | `Dict[str, Any]` | - |\n219: | `push_image` | `image_name`, `registry_url`, `username`, `password` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `RuntimeError`, `ValueError` |\n220: | `remove_image` | `image_name`, `force` | `bool` | - |\n221: \n222: ### Return Value Structures\n223: \n224: #### build_image() Return Value\n225: ```python\n226: {\n227:     \"image_name\": \"myagent:latest\",\n228:     \"image_id\": \"abc123def456\",\n229:     \"image_size\": \"2.00 GB\",\n230:     \"size_bytes\": 2147483648,\n231:     \"build_time\": 1712851200.123456\n232: }\n233: ```\n234: \n235: #### push_image() Return Value\n236: ```python\n237: {\n238:     \"pushed_image\": \"registry.example.com/username/myagent:latest\",\n239:     \"push_time\": \"1712851200.123456\"\n240: }\n241: ```\n242: \n243: #### get_image_info() Return Value\n244: ```python\n245: {\n246:     \"image_name\": \"myagent:latest\",\n247:     \"image_id\": \"abc123def456\",\n248:     \"image_size\": \"2.00 GB\",\n249:     \"size_bytes\": 2147483648\n250: }\n251: ```\n252: \n253: ## Verification\n254: \n255: ### Tests Pass\n256: \n257: ```bash\n258: cd cmd/cli\n259: python -m pytest tests/test_docker_service.py -v\n260: # Result: 45 passed, 2 skipped, 0 failed\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ### Coverage\n264: \n265: ```bash\n266: python -m pytest tests/test_docker_service.py --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service\n267: # Result: 98% coverage for docker_service.py\n268: ```\n269: \n270: ### Import Verification\n271: \n272: ```bash\n273: python -c \"from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService; print('✓ OK')\"\n274: # Result: ✓ OK\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ### Integration Verification\n278: \n279: ```bash\n280: python -m pytest tests/test_build_runtime.py tests/test_publish_runtime.py -v\n281: # Result: All tests pass\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ## Compliance with Design Specification\n285: \n286: ### Architecture Principles ✓\n287: \n288: 1. **Encapsulation of Complexity**: Docker SDK complexity wrapped in service layer\n289: 2. **Lazy Initialization**: Docker client created on first access\n290: 3. **Error Isolation**: Docker SDK exceptions wrapped with descriptive messages\n291: 4. **Security First**: Passwords never logged, path validation implemented\n292: 5. **Observability**: Verbose mode for detailed logging\n293: 6. **Idempotency**: All operations safe to repeat\n294: \n295: ### Security Measures ✓\n296: \n297: 1. **Credential Handling**: Passwords never logged or stored\n298: 2. **Path Validation**: Prevents directory traversal\n299: 3. **Input Validation**: All parameters validated\n300: 4. **Secure Logging**: No sensitive information in logs\n301: \n302: ### Error Handling ✓\n303: \n304: 1. **Descriptive Messages**: All errors include context\n305: 2. **Appropriate Exceptions**: RuntimeError for unrecoverable, warnings for recoverable\n306: 3. **Stack Traces**: Preserved in verbose mode\n307: 4. **Graceful Degradation**: Non-critical failures don't raise exceptions\n308: \n309: ### Documentation ✓\n310: \n311: 1. **Google-style Docstrings**: All methods documented\n312: 2. **Type Hints**: Complete type annotations\n313: 3. **Comments**: Inline comments for complex logic\n314: 4. **Examples**: Docstrings include usage examples\n315: \n316: ## Dependencies\n317: \n318: ### New Dependencies\n319: \n320: - `docker>=6.0.0` (Docker SDK for Python) - Already in pyproject.toml\n321: \n322: ### Existing Dependencies Used\n323: \n324: - `pathlib` - File path handling (standard library)\n325: - `logging` - Logging (standard library)\n326: - `typing` - Type annotations (standard library)\n327: - `time` - Timestamps (standard library)\n328: \n329: ## Acceptance Criteria\n330: \n331: All acceptance criteria from the proposal have been met:\n332: \n333: ### Core Functionality ✓\n334: \n335: - [x] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when Docker daemon is running\n336: - [x] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` when Docker daemon is stopped\n337: - [x] `build_image()` successfully builds images from Dockerfiles\n338: - [x] `build_image()` streams build logs to console\n339: - [x] `build_image()` supports build_args for proxy configuration\n340: - [x] `get_image_info()` returns correct image metadata\n341: - [x] `get_image_info()` formats size in human-readable format\n342: - [x] `push_image()` successfully pushes to Docker Hub with credentials\n343: - [x] `push_image()` handles registry URL retagging\n344: - [x] `remove_image()` removes images successfully\n345: - [x] `remove_image()` returns `False` on failure and logs warning\n346: \n347: ### Error Handling ✓\n348: \n349: - [x] Raises `RuntimeError` when Docker is unavailable\n350: - [x] Raises appropriate exceptions for build failures\n351: - [x] Handles authentication failures gracefully\n352: - [x] Logs detailed errors in verbose mode\n353: - [x] Provides user-friendly error messages\n354: \n355: ### Integration ✓\n356: \n357: - [x] BuildRuntime successfully uses DockerService for local builds\n358: - [x] PublishRuntime successfully uses DockerService for publishing\n359: - [x] Verbose flag is respected for logging\n360: - [x] Errors propagate correctly through runtime classes\n361: \n362: ### Testing ✓\n363: \n364: - [x] Unit tests for all public methods\n365: - [x] Mock Docker SDK for testing without Docker daemon\n366: - [x] Integration tests with real Docker daemon (skipped by default)\n367: - [x] Test proxy configuration via build_args\n368: - [x] Test registry authentication and push\n369: \n370: ## Conclusion\n371: \n372: The DockerService implementation is complete, fully tested, and ready for use. It provides a robust, secure, and well-documented abstraction layer for Docker operations in the AgentCube CLI toolkit. All design specifications have been met, and the implementation follows Python best practices with 98% test coverage.\n373: \n374: ### Key Achievements\n375: \n376: 1. **Complete Implementation**: All required methods implemented according to specification\n377: 2. **High Test Coverage**: 98% coverage with 47 comprehensive test cases\n378: 3. **Security First**: Secure credential handling and input validation\n379: 4. **Error Resilient**: Comprehensive error handling with descriptive messages\n380: 5. **Well Documented**: Google-style docstrings with examples\n381: 6. **Production Ready**: Integrated with existing BuildRuntime and PublishRuntime\n382: \n383: ### Next Steps\n384: \n385: The implementation is complete and ready for production use. No additional work is required for AR-024.\n386: \n387: ---\n388: \n389: **Implementation Date**: 2024-04-11\n390: **Test Coverage**: 98%\n391: **Status**: ✅ Complete\n\n(End of file - total 391 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\n\nSuccessfully implemented the DockerService encapsulation for the AgentCube CLI toolkit as specified in AR-024. The implementation provides a Pythonic abstraction layer over Docker SDK operations required by the CLI's `pack`, `build`, and `publish` workflows.\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files Modified/Created\n\n1. **cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py** - Main implementation\n   - Complete DockerService class with all required methods\n   - Comprehensive docstrings following Google style\n   - Input validation and security measures\n   - Error handling and logging\n\n2. **cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py** - Comprehensive test suite\n   - 47 test cases covering all functionality\n   - 98% code coverage\n   - Tests for success scenarios, error scenarios, and edge cases","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775871642625,"end":1775871642647}}}}
