{"type":"text","timestamp":1775871712463,"sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","part":{"id":"prt_d7a33ae46001rqUbCPpQWyfWAB","messageID":"msg_d7a338631001aM0BQmK1AupGKH","sessionID":"ses_285cdb4ddffem8xdXe9Ez0Bk8K","type":"text","text":"## AR-024 Archive Summary: DockerService 封装\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Status:** ✅ Complete\n\n---\n\n### ✅ What Was Completed\n\n**Core Implementation**\n- ✅ `DockerService` class with complete Pythonic abstraction layer over Docker SDK\n- ✅ All public methods: `check_docker_available()`, `build_image()`, `get_image_info()`, `push_image()`, `remove_image()`\n- ✅ Private helper methods: `_validate_build_paths()`, `_format_size()`, `_docker_login_sdk()`, `_tag_image_sdk()`\n- ✅ Lazy initialization pattern for Docker client\n- ✅ Google-style docstrings with type hints\n\n**Security & Error Handling**\n- ✅ Secure credential handling (passwords never logged or stored)\n- ✅ Path validation to prevent directory traversal attacks\n- ✅ Input validation for all parameters\n- ✅ Comprehensive exception handling with descriptive error messages\n- ✅ Graceful degradation for non-critical failures\n\n**Testing**\n- ✅ 45 unit tests passing (2 skipped integration tests requiring Docker daemon)\n- ✅ 98% test coverage for `docker_service.py`\n- ✅ Tests for success scenarios, error scenarios, and edge cases\n- ✅ Mock-based testing without requiring Docker daemon\n\n**Integration**\n- ✅ Integrated with `BuildRuntime` for local builds\n- ✅ Integrated with `PublishRuntime` for image publishing\n- ✅ Verbose mode respected for logging across runtime classes\n- ✅ Proper error propagation through runtime layers\n\n---\n\n### ⏸️ What Was Deferred\n\n**Optional Enhancement Tasks** (non-blocking for production use)\n- ⏸️ Integration tests requiring real Docker daemon (2 tests marked as skipped)\n- ⏸️ Multi-version compatibility testing (Python 3.10, 3.11, 3.12)\n- ⏸️ Multi-version Docker compatibility testing (20.10.x, 24.0.x, 25.0.x)\n- ⏸️ Performance benchmarking and optimization\n- ⏸️ Resource cleanup testing for failure scenarios\n- ⏸️ Concurrent operation stress testing\n- ⏸️ Extended environment variable testing (DOCKER_HOST, DOCKER_TLS_VERIFY, etc.)\n- ⏸️ Timeout behavior fine-tuning\n\n**Documentation** (could be added later)\n- ⏸️ User-facing README for `agentcube/services` module\n- ⏸️ Troubleshooting guide with common error solutions\n\n**Code Quality** (nice-to-have but not blocking)\n- ⏸️ flake8/black/mypy linting and type checking (manual review completed instead)\n- ⏸️ Additional cleanup of any TODO/FIXME comments\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Test Results\n\n```\nTests: 45 passed, 2 skipped, 0 failed\nCoverage: 98% for docker_service.py\nExecution time: 1.01s\n```\n\n**Skipped Tests:**\n- `test_e2e_build_real_image` - requires Docker daemon\n- `test_e2e_push_real_image` - requires Docker daemon and registry\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Acceptance Criteria Status\n\nAll core acceptance criteria met:\n- ✅ Docker availability checking\n- ✅ Image building with proxy support\n- ✅ Image metadata retrieval\n- ✅ Image pushing with authentication\n- ✅ Image removal with error handling\n- ✅ Integration with BuildRuntime and PublishRuntime\n- ✅ Verbose logging support\n\n---\n\n### 🎯 Production Readiness\n\nThe DockerService implementation is **production-ready** with no blocking issues. All deferred items are optional enhancements that can be addressed in future iterations without impacting current functionality.","time":{"start":1775871712460,"end":1775871712460}}}
